Red Bull's Dutch driver Max Verstappen drives during a practice session. AFP/Kamran Jebreili MIAMI - Two of Formula 1’s top drivers are pushing for a race in Africa. World champion and Red Bull driver Max Verstappen has backed Mercedes’ Lewis Hamilton's calls for F1 to return to South Africa. READ: Former F1 team boss calls for SA Grand Prix Both drivers have suggested Kyalami as the desired racing circuit. Almost three decades have passed since the last race took place in Africa. Apart from Hamilton and Verstappen, many believe it's time for Formula 1 to visit the continent as part of a 20+ race season.